CourseList.Name: Alamo Sea
CourseList.Description: Gravel roads around Alamo Sea.

CourseList.Name: Central 8
CourseList.Description: Escape the hustle and bustle of city life with a ride in the central county of Los Santos.

CourseList.Name: Davis Quartz
CourseList.Description: Take a spin around the terraced mining quarry of Davis Quartz.

CourseList.Name: Docklands
CourseList.Description: Explore the harbor area of Los Santos with warehouses, shipyards and container terminals.

CourseList.Name: Downtown
CourseList.Description: Take a city tour through downtown Los Santos.

CourseList.Name: East Los Santos
CourseList.Description: Discover the eastern part of Los Santos with smaller sub-districts and neighbourhoods.

CourseList.Name: El Burro Heights
CourseList.Description: Dig deep on the oil fields in the El Burro Heights area.

CourseList.Name: Foothills
CourseList.Description: Visit some of the scenic highlights of Los Santos with some good climbs and fast descents.

CourseList.Name: Full Circle
CourseList.Description: The course starts at the Casino and then heads North to circle the Grapeseed area before ascending into the Vinewood hills and heading back through town to the Casino.

CourseList.Name: Franklin's Radio Tower Kom
CourseList.Description: Zig Zag up to the radio tower from Franklin's house, very steep at the top.
CourseList.Notes: At the 6km mark the gps is off by 1 block but it corrects itself, can be heavy traffic so watch out!

CourseList.Name: Grapeseed
CourseList.Description: Fuel your next ride with a tour through the fields of Grapeseed.

CourseList.Name: Gravelfondo
CourseList.Description: A great selection of gravel roads for an epic ride through the central & midwest area.

CourseList.Name: Great Chaparral
CourseList.Description: Enjoy the best switchbacks up and down the hills of Great Chaparral.

CourseList.Name: Hills and Valleys 8
CourseList.Description: Figure 8 course through Los Santos hills & valleys.

CourseList.Name: Land Act Dam Loop
CourseList.Description: Quick loop around Los Santos Pumping Station.

CourseList.Name: Los Santos Hills
CourseList.Description: Roads around Los Santos hills.

CourseList.Name: Los Santos Road Rally
CourseList.Description: Gravel and tarmac roads through Los Santos.

CourseList.Name: Marlowe Vineyards
CourseList.Description: Taste the trails in Marlowe Vineyards. Use the brake to slow down to 30km/20mi on sharp  bends to avoid crashes.

CourseList.Name: Motown - Less Country
CourseList.Description: Course starts & ends at the Observatory and tours the central part of downtown Los Santos and the beach area past the pier. Use the brake to slow down to 30km/20mi before taking the right turn onto the pedestrian mall to avoid a crash.

CourseList.Name: Mount Chilliad
CourseList.Description: Get an adrenaline rush on the trails around Mount Chilliad. Use the brake to slow down to 30km/20mi on sharp bends to avoid crashes.

CourseList.Name: Mount Josiah
CourseList.Description: Lap around Mount Josiah.

CourseList.Name: Mount Josiah & Alamo Sea
CourseList.Description: Eight shaped route around Mount Josiah &  Alamo Sea.

CourseList.Name: Palomino Highlands
CourseList.Description: Roads in Palomino Highlands area.

CourseList.Name: Ports Oil Slick & Golf Stick
CourseList.Description: Route around ports, airport, oil fields & golf course.
CourseList.Notes: The course crosses a railway line 4 times, at 6.3km (3.9mi), 17.7km (11mi), 18.4km (11.4mi) and 18.6km (11.6mi). The first 2 are managed by crossing barriers, so if you see them lowering, be prepared to stop. The last 2, as you enter the port are not, but I've never seen a train on them.

CourseList.Name: Redwood Lights
CourseList.Description: Build your fitness on Redwood Lights construction site.

CourseList.Name: Richman Golf
CourseList.Description: Take an exclusive lap on the Los Santos golf club.

CourseList.Name: Route 68
CourseList.Description: Cruise on route 68 through rural desert areas and the small town of Harmony.

CourseList.Name: Senora Desert
CourseList.Description: Ride through Senora Desert, a great place to experience hot temperatures and to get lost.

CourseList.Name: Suburb Crit
CourseList.Description: Loop in East Los Santos.

CourseList.Name: The Tourist
CourseList.Description: A sightseeing tour through Los Santos.

CourseList.Name: Tour Los Santos
CourseList.Description: Big loop around Los Santos.

CourseList.Name: Tracks, Terminals & Tarmac
CourseList.Description: This course starts at the terminal docks and lets you ride on some old decommissioned R&R tracks as well as cruising on the main runway at Airport before heading out of town for a short climb in the Vinewood hills and back to the terminal docks.

CourseList.Name: Vinewood Heights
CourseList.Description: A hilly zigzag through ritzy Vinewood Heights.

CourseList.Name: Vinewood Racetrack
CourseList.Description: Loop on Vinewood racetrack.

CourseList.Name: West Coast
CourseList.Description: Ride through Raton Canyon and along Zancudo River on the west coast.

CourseList.Name: Windy Hills
CourseList.Description: Get some fresh air on RON Alternates Wind Farm.
